      "description": "This 2008 Porsche 911 Carrera S represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated 997.1 engineering. The 3.8L flat-six power plant exhibits flawless compression across all cylinders, with a documented service history confirming zero bore scoring and a proactive IMS solution. Power is routed through a precise six-speed manual transaxle paired with a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. The Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) system has been impeccably preserved, ensuring razor-sharp turn-in and exceptional lateral stability. This example remains in showroom-fresh condition, featuring original paint with consistent micron depth and an undercarriage devoid of thermal cycling wear or oxidation. A true turn-key, collector-grade specimen for the analog purist.",
